Definition: an adviser to the court on some matter of law who is not a party to the case
Example: usually someone who wants to influence the outcome of a lawsuit involving matters of wide public interest
Synonyms: friend_of_the_court, adviser, noun, group, law, c, an, to, the, court, on, some, matter, of, who, is, not, a, party, case, usually, someone, wants, influence, outcome, lawsuit, involving, matters, wide, public, interest
Category: noun.person
